.TH BW-LOCK 1 "January 2026" "Bitwarden CLI" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bw-lock \- lock the vault and destroy active session keys

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bw lock

.SH DESCRIPTION
Lock the vault and destroy all active session keys. This provides security by
removing decrypted vault data from memory without fully logging out.

After locking, use \fBbw unlock\fP to unlock the vault again. You do not need
to re-enter your email or re-authenticate with two-factor authentication.

.SH OPTIONS
This command has no specific options. See \fBbw\fP(1) for global options.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Lock the vault:
.nf
$ bw lock
Your vault is locked.
.fi

.SH NOTES
.TP
\(bu
Locking is faster than logging out when you need temporary security.
.TP
\(bu
The \fBBW_SESSION\fP environment variable becomes invalid after locking.
.TP
\(bu
You must be logged in to lock the vault.
.TP
\(bu
Locking clears the master key and vault data from memory.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Vault successfully locked.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (e.g., not logged in).

